Spring Framework

Spring is a lightweight java framework enterprise 

Features :
  -> Dependency Injection
  -> Aspect-oriented programming
  ->Spring MVC, Spring Data, Spring Cloud, Spring security

Web application, restful api, data processing application, security authentication, messaging-event 
 
DI, IOC, AOP 

Spring Boot : 

Dependency Injection:- 

IOC - Inversion of Control:-

Class Employee{
 Address address;
 Employee(){
      address = new Address();       //Tightly coupled 
  }
  ....
  ....
  ....
}

Class Employee{
   Address address;
    Employee(Address address){
      this.address = address;       //Looselly coupled
  }
}


@Autowired
Address address;  //Feild Injection

Spring Bean:

A bean is object managed by Spring container.

@Service
public class publicService{
   public void sayHello(){
      sysout("hello from spring");
  }
}

Constructor Injection:
----------------------

@Component
public class car{
    private Engine engine;
   
    @Autowired
    Public car(Engine engine){
       this.engine = engine;
  }
}


-> code reading
-> tight coupling
-> reusability

Bean Lifecycle:

Container started 
       |
Bean instantiated  //declare
       |
dependencies injected
       |
Custom init() //method
       |
Bean is fully ready to use
       |

Custom utility method
       |
custom destroy() //method


Spring IOC Container

->Creating objects (Beans)
->Configuring dependencies Dependency Injection(DI)
->Managing the entire lifecycle of beans
->xml (pom.xml), application properties, Annotations

Spring ApplicationContext 
   AnnotationconfigWeb
   XmlWebApplication
   FileSystemXmlApplication


Spring web- SpringWeb, Jdbc - springjdbc, SpringData, SpringSecurity, 
    Farmework - Hibernate, JPA
SpringMVC - CRUD


Spring Boot Architecture:

Presentation Layer: 
      HTTP - 
      Rest Api -
      Request validation -
      Authentication
      JSON
      Forwards validated requests to Business layer
Annotation: @Controller

Business Layer:
      Implement the business rules, workflow
      processes validates data
      Handles the authentication and authorization logic (Spring security)
      Manages transaction @Transactional

Annotation: @Service
      
Persistence Layer:
     CRUD 
     database transactions
     Sql, NoSql
     Spring Data JPA, Hibernate, R2Db, H2

Annotation: @Repository
     
Database Layer:
     Contains Actual application database 
     MySql, PostgreSql, Oracle, Server -SQL
     MangoDB, FireBase, DynamoDB - NoSQL
     Cloud